[[div]]
[[[SCP-1048]]] - An animate teddy bear that reconstitutes matter into duplicates of itself.
[[/div]]
[[div]]
[*http://scp-int.wikidot.com/scp-1054-ru K-1054-RU] - An airplane engine that produces a variety of organisms resembling crows with anomalous capabilities.
[[/div]]
[[div]]
Lifeforms produced by K-1054-RU's "low throttle", "cruise", and  "high throttle" settings are attacked and repurposed into copies of SCP-1048. When K-1054-RU shifts into its "emergency" setting, the resulting murder of crows abduct SCP-1048 copies, feeding them into the engine. Due to the sheer number of entities within the chamber at all times, the original SCP-1048 has not been seen in over a decade.
[[/div]]

[[div]]
= [[[scp-2521|●●|●●●●●|●●|●]]]
[[image http://scp-wiki.wdfiles.com/local--files/fragment%3Aketer-duty-2/scp_number.jpg size="small"]]
[[/div]]
[[div]]
[[[scp-5242|K-INTEGER]]] - A HAZARD CONSTRUCT that abstracts the identities of media of communication which describe it concretely.
[[/div]]
[[div]]
[[image https://web.archive.org/web/20210611002853im_/https://scp-sandbox-3.wdfiles.com/local--files/collab%3Aketer-duty/scp_number2.png width="100%"]]
In return, the spread of K-INTEGER's abstraction effect is limited by its need to now elude capture.
[[/div]]

[[div]]
[[[SCP-106]]] - A malicious humanoid entity that corrodes all forms of matter, bringing prey into a pocket dimension to torture and kill.
[[/div]]
[[div]]
[[[scp-3333|K-3333]]] - A fire lookout tower whose floors extend upwards in perpetuity. Inhabited by hostile lifeforms.
[[/div]]
[[div]]
SCP-106 hunts the entities residing in K-3333; however, attempts to draw these entities into its pocket dimension invariably result in SCP-106 re-emerging within K-3333. This has resulted in SCP-106's behavior growing more erratic and agitated; at one point, they were observed tearing a vulpine inhabitant of K-3333 in half in an apparent fit of rage. This behavior is encouraged by various taunting behaviors of K-3333 inhabitants, who cajole SCP-106 and lure him onto higher floors.
[[/div]]

[[div]]
[[[SCP-2718|SCP- ]]] - The subjective perception of death in perpetuity.
[[/div]]
[[div]]
[[[scp-3980|K-3980]]] - A transmissible state of being that subverts known traits of the life/death dichotomy.
[[/div]]
[[div]]
= {{sleep now, children}}
[[/div]]

[[div]]
[[[scp-231|SCP-231-7]]] - The sole survivor of an anomalous ritual perpetrated by the Children of the Scarlet King. The removal or delivery of foeti from other victims have led to an increasing amount of devastation; were SCP-231-7 to follow suit, an XK-level event would occur.
[[/div]]
[[div]]
[[[scp-4666|K-4666]]] - An ancient humanoid that abducts children, producing toys from their bodily remains.
[[/div]]
[[div]]
Once every twenty-four hours, SCP-231-7 is subjected to [DATA EXPUNGED], which has effectively replaced procedure 110-Montauk, while also lessening the psychological impact on SCP-231-7. K-4666 collects toys resulting from this interaction and places them into his sack. The sack undulates with the motions of its inhabitants.
[[/div]]


