[[div]]
[[[scp-3999|K-3999]]] - N/A
[[/div]]
[[div]]
The exact process of containment is not fully understood; the corpse of Researcher Talloran is suspended in the middle of a chamber. The sound of a wooden baseball bat dragging against concrete can be heard on occasion.
[[/div]]

[[div]]
[[[SCP-1739]]] - A parauniversal containment apparatus in the form of a Dell laptop. Its primary program is used to input a time between 01/01/2004 and the present. Doing so will displace the user into the past, creating a divergent timeline. This universe will then be fed on by an unknown entity, represented on the computer as a graphic of a woman unchaining a dog and tossing a ball.
[[/div]]
[[div]]
[[[http://www.scpwiki.com/scp-5243|K-5243]]] - A retrocausal containment breach contained to Site-43. Must be re-enacted perfectly each year to prevent the creation of dead timelines.
[[/div]]
[[div]]
SCP-1739 has been used to create a divergent timeline in which its activation is entangled with K-5243. This timeline is consumed soon after its creation, but reconstitutes annually due to the recurrence of K-5243. SCP-1739 displays an animation of a dog chasing its tail.
[[/div]]

[[div]]
[[[SCP-2316]]] - A lake containing human corpses floating at its surface. Possesses cognitohazardous traits that prey upon familiarity and kinship.
[[/div]]
[[div]]
[[[scp-5856|K-5856]]] - A sociokinetic humanoid that can manipulate social bonds.
[[/div]]
[[div]]
SCP-2316's effects are malleable to K-5856, which remains lakeside as it does not recognize the bodies in the water.
[[/div]]

[[div]]
[[[SCP-469]]] - A humanoid entity encased within countless furled wings that grow in number with the absorption of sound.
[[/div]]
[[div]]
[[[http://scp-int.wikidot.com/scp-es-002|K-ES-002]]] - A parasitic species of soundwaves.
[[/div]]
[[div]]
SCP-469 unfurls its wings to capture instances of K-ES-002, rendering the chamber silent as it grows. K-ES-002 then uses SCP-469 as a medium for reproduction, with juvenile instances being released into SCP-469's chamber at irregular intervals. An evolutionary pattern has been noticed among K-ES-002; while originally at an inaudible frequency below 17hz, K-ES-002 is currently audible, and resembles sounds produced by individuals undergoing glossolalia.
[[/div]]

[[div]]
[[[SCP-2719]]] - A metaphysical pointer capable of redefining or sending concepts inside.
[[/div]]
[[div]]
[[[SCP-3125|K-3125]]] - Unknown concept with some form of agency.
[[/div]]
[[div]]
SCP-2719 is in a constant state of flux due to attempts by K-3125 to reassert its foci from within; all attempts to go outside result in it becoming inside.
[[/div]]

